Donnacha O&rsquo;Brien reports his star filly&nbsp;Fancy Blue&nbsp;to be &quot;in great shape&quot; following her victory in the Nassau Stakes at Goodwood.<br />
<br />
Speaking after saddling a winner at Gowran Park on Wednesday, O&rsquo;Brien said: &ldquo;Fancy Blue is in great shape and still being aimed at Irish Champions Weekend. It will be either there or France, which is the same weekend.&rdquo;

Tatical remains on course to test his powers at Group One level in the Prix Morny at&nbsp;Deauville&nbsp;on Sunday week<br />
<br />
John Warren, the Queen&rsquo;s racing manager, said: &ldquo;Tactical did a nice piece of work this morning and is on course for the Prix Morny on August 23, which has been his target since winning the July Stakes.&rdquo;

